<subSubSection id="7CECAE83DB20FFDA8C839F1044E2FD86" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3449FD08DB20FFDA8C839F1044E2FD86" blockId="15.[151,1436,375,1013]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8C839F104113FE36" bold="true" box="[151,273,375,400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species and 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8DC39F1E4232FE36" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Gibran" authorityYear="2017" box="[471,560,375,400]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meloi">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8DC39F1E4232FE36" box="[471,560,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. meloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct from all remaining 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8F859F10442AFE36" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1948" box="[913,1064,375,400]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8F859F10442AFE36" box="[913,1064,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Tetraglossula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species for the metasoma largely or partly orange or red. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8E539FFA42AFFE12" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[583,685,412,436]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fucosa">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8E539FFA42AFFE12" box="[583,685,412,436]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. fucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are generally shorter than 
<quantity id="F30E50EDDB20FFDA8FCA9FFB4433FE12" box="[990,1073,412,436]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
, wings are hyaline (
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA89039FFA4573FE13" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Gibran" authorityYear="2017" box="[1303,1393,412,437]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meloi">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA89039FFA4573FE13" box="[1303,1393,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. meloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger and more robust bees, wings are fuscous). The male S7 of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8F6D9FA643DDFE7E" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[889,991,448,472]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fucosa">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8F6D9FA643DDFE7E" box="[889,991,448,472]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. fucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a broad trapezoid basal lobe (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB20FFDA897B9FD840B1FE5A" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
N; see comments below), only comparable to that of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8F369F8243BBFE5B" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[802,953,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8F369F8243BBFE5B" box="[802,953,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. anthracina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose general appearance is completely distinct from that of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8D699C6E41DDFD86" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[381,479,520,544]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fucosa">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8D699C6E41DDFD86" box="[381,479,520,544]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. fucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA8DE69C6E428AFD86" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[498,648,519,544]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8DE69C6E428AFD86" box="[498,648,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. anthracina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are black bees, the pubescence is all black or dusky).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7CECAE83DB20FFDA8CD39C4B4451FD16" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" type="description">
<paragraph id="3449FD08DB20FFDA8CD39C4B4451FD16" blockId="15.[151,1436,375,1013]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA8CD39C4B423CFDE2" box="[199,574,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Male genitalia and hidden sterna</emphasis>
S6–S8: 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB20FFDA8E899C4B42EDFDE2" box="[669,751,556,581]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Figs 14</figureCitation>
M–P, 15J–L. Line drawings of male T7, S6–S8 and genitalia can be found in Michener (1989, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB20FFDA8E059C284262FDCE" box="[529,608,591,616]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[222,1356,971,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[204,1383,951,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tetraglossula deltivaga Ogloblin, 1948, ♀, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil [RPSP- 121831]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841552/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A–I). Basal lobe of S7 (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB20FFDA8F7A9C2843BCFDCE" box="[878,958,591,616]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
N) broad, less pilose that in 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB20FFDA88EA9C364597FDCE" baseAuthorityName="Michener" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[1278,1429,591,616]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB20FFDA88EA9C364597FDCE" box="[1278,1429,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">T. anthracina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and trapezoid, partly superposed with the apical lobe; medial sclerotized region positioned proximally to apical and basal lobes of S7 short. Apical lobe of S8 subequal to disc of S 
<quantity id="F30E50EDDB20FFDA8F4C9CFF4380FD16" box="[856,898,663,688]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="15" pageNumber="536" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
profile (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB20FFDA8FF79CF04436FD16" box="[995,1076,663,688]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
P).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
