<collectingCountry id="4CE1BD98DB20FFDA8FAA9D084412FC2E" box="[958,1040,879,904]" name="Bolivia" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion id="F63233EADB20FFDA88529D1744ACFC2E" box="[1094,1198,880,904]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">
<collectingCountry id="4CE1BD98DB20FFDA88529D1744ACFC2E" box="[1094,1198,880,904]" name="Paraguay" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
are based on a single female specimen each [
<collectionCode id="52E765CDDB20FFDA8D889DF341F1FC0A" box="[412,499,916,940]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">USNM</collectionCode>
] do not appear to have significant morphological differences from individuals from the 
<typeStatus id="EB4D43AADB20FFDA8CD69DDF40F0FC76" box="[194,242,952,976]" pageId="15" pageNumber="536">type</typeStatus>
locality, other than color variation (slightly lighter color in the female from San Borja and darker in the specimen from San Bernardino).
</paragraph>
